In this speech, President Donald Trump addresses the Israeli American Council and expresses his commitment to the strong relationship between the United States and Israel. He thanks Miriam and Sheldon Adelson for their support and highlights the importance of fostering an unbreakable bond between the two countries. The President discusses his actions in support of Israel, including recognizing Jerusalem as the capital of Israel and moving the U.S. Embassy there, recognizing Israeli sovereignty over the Golan Heights, and withdrawing from the Iran nuclear deal. He also condemns anti-Semitism and pledges to fight against it, both domestically and internationally. The President recognizes Adela Cojab, a recent graduate who took legal action against her university for failing to protect its Jewish community from harassment and attacks. He also highlights the contributions of Jewish Americans to the country and ends the speech with a prayer for the military, veterans, and the State of Israel.